This paper deals with error correction in compressed sensing, which involves the recovery of a sparse vector from corrupted measurements. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) which are relevant for the algorithms used in the paper. Additionally, the paper discusses the threshold for successful recovery, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI).
